Top Stories (January 4)

SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA EDISON CONDEMNS CALIFORNIA COMMISSION'S RATE PLAN
Southern California Edison, a unit of Edison International, condemned the 
California Public Utilities Commission's proposed decision on an interim rate 
increase.
http://199.97.97.79/IMDS%PMADJN0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/djn/2001/
01/04/eng-djn/eng-djn_000028_145_788091630675

BUSH WON'T ADDRESS CALIFORNIA POWER CRISIS UNTIL IN OFFICE
President-elect George W. Bush, while "worried" about the California 
power-supply crisis, won't attempt to weigh into the thorny problem until 
after he takes office Jan. 20, a Bush spokesman told reporters Thursday.
http://199.97.97.79/IMDS%PMADJN0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/djn/2001/
01/04/eng-djn/eng-djn_144027_155_607858868316

PSEG POWER PRESENTS PROPOSAL FOR 1100MW PLANT - PROPOSED COMBINED CYCLE, 
NATURAL GAS-FUELED POWER PLANT TO BE LOCATED IN ARCADIA, OHIO
PSEG Power LLC yesterday presented at a public meeting a proposal for a 1,100 
megawatt (MW) natural gas-fueled power plant to be located in Arcadia, Ohio.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMANAT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/comtex/2
001/01/04/pr/0000-0401-ny-pseg-power-plant

TEXAS ENERGY COALITION LOOKS TO BRING COMPETITION TO STATE ELECTRIC UTILITIES
A statewide coalition of energy producers hopes to lower the costs of doing 
business in Texas by consolidating electricity purchases under state rules to 
bring competition to Texas electric utilities.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMAKRT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/knightri
dder/2001/01/04/krtbn/0000-0024-AX-UTILITIES

ENERGY NORTHWEST SELLS SATSOP SITE
Energy Northwest's executive board meeting in Seattle Wednesday approved a 
land sale at its Satsop nuclear site west of Olympia to Duke Energy North 
America, which plans to build a power plant there.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMANAT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/tricityh
erald/2001/01/04/eng-tricity_2000/eng-tricity_2000_174504_90_2507364121266

